				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Gay By Choice
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1725117">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Goladus</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=2f1c020babc86faf2681e53c14599bb3&amp;p=1725042#post1725042" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">The men, on average, responded genitally in what Chivers terms &#8220;category specific&#8221; ways. Males who identified themselves as straight swelled while gazing at heterosexual or lesbian sex and while watching the masturbating and exercising women. They were mostly unmoved when the screen displayed only men. Gay males were aroused in the opposite categorical pattern. Any expectation that the animal sex would speak to something primitive within the men seemed to be mistaken; neither straights nor gays were stirred by the bonobos. And for the male participants, the subjective ratings on the keypad matched the readings of the plethysmograph. The men&#8217;s minds and genitals were in agreement.<br />
<br />
All was different with the women. No matter what their self-proclaimed sexual orientation, they showed, on the whole, strong and swift genital arousal when the screen offered men with men, women with women and women with men.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Yup. I've read studies like this before and it only strengthens the point: Men have no control over what they are turned on by - and women are sometimes so disconnected they don't even realise what turns them on; so given that your sexual orientation is determined by what turns you on rather than who you sleep with it's obviously even less of a choice for them.<br />
 <br />
(Of course, not that it's news to anyone who's ever been in a relationship that being turned on is a much more complicated process for women than for men - involving sometimes disconnected physical, emotional and intellectual drives. This study obviously only considered the physical side. <br />
<br />
Still, guys have much simpler knobs and switches than women (PI). If there's two lovers and the man is playing too much EQ and the woman wants sex, all she has to do is walk up to the computer, slowly take off all her clothes and announce she'll be in the bedroom. A guy doing the same thing with a woman playing too much EQ would get laughed at <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Stick Out Tongue" class="inlineimg" /> (Although she will sometimes also buy it!))
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
